---
/**
 * Sources — the single numbered register every sourced-claim and footnote
 * superscript on the page links to (Mercury's footnote-ledger pattern, and
 * the practical face of the no-invented-metrics rule; adoption #5 extends it
 * with claim-qualifying footnotes). CSS counters number the superscripts in
 * DOM order, so entries here must stay in the same order as the .src-note
 * anchors appear on the page.
 */
---
<section class="sources" id="sources" aria-label="Sources and footnotes">
  <div class="container">
    <h2 class="sources__title">Sources &amp; Footnotes</h2>
    <ol class="sources__list">
      <li id="src-1">
        UK Finance, card spending data, 2024 — total UK debit and credit card spending £1,046bn
        (£797bn debit, £249bn credit) across 31.4bn transactions.
        <a href="https://www.ukfinance.org.uk/news-and-insight/press-release/ps1-trillion-worth-uk-card-transactions-in-2024" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ukfinance.org.uk</a>
      </li>
      <li id="src-2">
        UK Finance, UK Payment Markets 2025 — cash fell to 9% of UK payments in 2024, from 48% in 2014.
        <a href="https://www.ukfinance.org.uk/policy-and-guidance/reports-and-publications/uk-payment-markets-2025" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ukfinance.org.uk</a>
      </li>
      <li id="src-3">
        Small Business Commissioner and Department for Business &amp; Trade research, 2025 — business
        owners spend an average of 86 hours a year chasing unpaid invoices.
        <a href="https://www.smallbusinesscommissioner.gov.uk/late-payments-research-2/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">smallbusinesscommissioner.gov.uk</a>
      </li>
      <li id="src-4">
        The two-working-day figure covers your core payment page, from your merchant account being
        approved. Invoicing, accounting bridges and reconciliation follow in as little as five
        working days.
      </li>
      <li id="src-5">
        Payments are processed by FCA-regulated partners such as Stripe, Adyen and Checkout.com.
        SettlePay builds and manages your payment page and never holds your funds.
      </li>
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>
